			<div class="post">
				<h3>Transmission built in.</h3>
				<div class="date"><img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: <strong>Mon Nov 01, 2010 4:37 pm</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>alias_neo</strong></div>
				<div class="content">I just found out (after having already installed a custom transmission daemon) that this GoFlex already has transmission.<br /><br />If you edit /etc/features.conf (and enable everything that's not there) including <br /><br />&quot;supportsTransmission&quot; = 1<br /><br />This will add a nice torrent icon to the Web interface and you can use Transmission client.<br />Now I just need to figure out how to get everything else working. (Flick, Facebook, &quot;Premium&quot;)</div>
			</div>
			<hr />
		
			<div class="post">
				<h3>Re: Transmission built in.</h3>
				<div class="date"><img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: <strong>Sat Nov 06, 2010 11:16 am</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>alias_neo</strong></div>
				<div class="content">It turns out that enabling Facebook and Flickr options was also as simple as just turning the option to &quot;1&quot; (on) i the same features.conf file.<br /><br />Enjoy.</div>
			</div>
			<hr />
		
			<div class="post">
				<h3>Re: Transmission built in.</h3>
				<div class="date"><img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: <strong>Sat Nov 20, 2010 7:32 pm</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>earthdan</strong></div>
				<div class="content">Sorry I'm really new at this.......how do I get to that config file?<br /><br />Step by step would be amazing if anybody has a chance!!!<br /><br />Thanks a lot,<br /><br />Dan<br /><br />Edit: So I got to the features.conf file but it seems that I can't edit it using the vi command<br /><br />I am typing vi features.conf which displays the contents of the file, then I go to the supporttransmission entry at the bottom and set it to 1, but after that it just sits there. Is there something that I need to do in order for it to save?</div>
			</div>
			<hr />
		
			<div class="post">
				<h3>Re: Transmission built in.</h3>
				<div class="date"><img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: <strong>Sun Nov 21, 2010 7:49 am</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>FrankM</strong></div>
				<div class="content">Hi and Welcome Dan,<br /><br />So if i understand correctly you opened features.conf with vi from there it should not be to hard. <br /><br />Move your cursor to the bottom of the file.<br />Press the &lt;i&gt; button which makes it possible to insert characters (bottom line of your screen will read -- INSERT --)<br />Now you can add a line with supportTransmission=1 when you are done editing hit &lt;esc&gt;.<br />if you now type :wq you will save and exit the file if something went wrong and you dont want to save you can use :q!<br /><br />Good luck<br />Frank</div>
			</div>
			<hr />
		
			<div class="post">
				<h3>Re: Transmission built in.</h3>
				<div class="date"><img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: <strong>Sun Nov 21, 2010 9:32 am</strong></div>
