				<div class="content">Thanks for the reply Frank!<br /><br />I tried to do exactly as you said but for some reason the changes weren't sticking. So I searched around and eventually found the &quot;sudo&quot; command. So I typed sudo vi features.conf (while in the etc dir) and then applied what you said....and voila it stuck. <br /><br />Thanks so much for your helpful post (and the OP!!), I'm really loving being able to run torrents while my computer is off. <br /><br />Is there anything else in the features file that would be worthwhile to enable? I enabled facebook but what is that &quot;premium&quot; that the OP was talking about?<br /><br />cheers,<br />Dan<br /><br />edit: I enabled the havemobile, and it looks like I can access my goflex from my ipad or blackberry!! Doesn't look like I can really do anything with the access tho, as when I try to click on any file it just boots me back to the main page where all I can see is the shares and Seagate share.<br /><br />Has any one figured out how to access the torrent interface from a mobile or while on a different network?<br /><br />Also, does anybody know how to change the upload speed of the transmission client? Ideally I would like to cap the speed so it doesn't bog down my network.<br /><br />cheers,<br />Dan</div>
